                        <Section Name="HelpCreateSection" FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" Foreground="#a0a0a0">

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    ATM ALERTS
                                </Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                The ATM ALERTS application creates custom mulitiple time frame scans on ATM Indicators and Conditions in five easy steps.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Once constructed, ATM Alerts can automatically
                                notify you when your custom condition is “true.”
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                ATM Alerts are built with Bloomberg’s global range of market data or with your personal PRTU or EQS.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" />

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    CREATE ALERTS
                                </Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Creating an Alert is an easy five-step process.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                The first time you open ATM Alerts, an Example Alert template will pre-populated.   The Example Alert is a working copy and will scan the individual
                                equities of the OEX Index for the FT Turns Up as well as the opposite Down condition.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Should you decide to delete the Example Alert, a
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    RESTORE EXAMPLE
                                </Run>
                                button will appear at the top right of the application.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Add a new alert by clicking on the
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    ADD NEW ALERT
                                </Run>
                                button.  This will open the ATM ALERT SETUP Dialog Box.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Complete each of the following steps:
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        Step 1: Select Your Security List
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        Step 2: Select Your ATM Conditions
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        Step 3: Change or Save Your Alert's Name
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        Step 4: Turn Alert Notification ON | OFF and determine if you want the Application to be on top of all other applications when an Alert occurs.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        Step 5: Determine how often the Alert should calculate.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" />

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    STEP 1:
                                </Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                In Step 1, you chose the list of securities that you wish to scan by checking the box next to it's name.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                For your custom list of securities, you can select individual groups, or you can assemble a file from one or more groups.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Asset Class and Geographical location categorize the Security List Navigation. Also, you can choose the list of
                                securities from any of your individual EQS or PRTU lists
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" />

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    STEP 2:
                                </Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                In Step 2, you chose the ATM Conditions for your Alert from a list of pre-defined ATM Conditions and Time Frames.
                                Select as many ATM Conditions as you wish, but conditions are “AND” together, which means all your requirements
                                have to be “TRUE” for a result to occur.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                To add a condition, select the white triangle next to the condition group header, which will open the full list of
                                ATM Conditions available for that group.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Select all the conditions that you wish your to Alert to be “TRUE” by it’s Time Frame.
                            </Paragraph>


                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" />

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    STEP 3:
                                </Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                ATM Alerts automatically names your alert as you build it. You can change the default name by highlighting
                                it and typing your desired name.   Click the
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    'SAVE'
                                </Run>
                                button when finished.
                            </Paragraph>


                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" />

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    STEP 4:
                                </Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                ATM Alerts Notification is a two-step process.  First - decide if you want to be Alerted
                                once a symbol meets your condition requirements.  If you do, select the
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    'CHECKBOX'
                                </Run>
                                just to the right of &quot;Turn Notification ON&quot;.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Second - determine if you want the new alert to push the
                                ATMML application to the top of all other applications each time there is a new alert. If you do, select the
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    'CHECKBOX'
                                </Run>
                                located just to the right of &quot;Alert on Top at Notification&quot;
                            </Paragraph>


                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" />

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    STEP 5:
                                </Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                To set the time – in minutes - between condition calculations, change the numeric value in the Textbox. The default is 5 minutes.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" />

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    REPLICATE
                                </Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                An additional method to add a new ATM Alert is with the feature '
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    REPLICATE
                                </Run>
                                '.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Replicate will duplicate an ATM Alert.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                To Replicate an ATM Alert, right-clicked on the title bar of the Alert. This action will duplicate the selected Alert.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Make changes to the replicated Alert by
                                selecting the
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    Edit &#x1F589; Icon.
                                </Run>
                                Once your edits are complete, click the
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    'SAVE'
                                </Run>
                                button.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" />

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#ff8c00">
                                    START
                                </Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                Select the
                                <Run FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="PaleGreen">
                                    'START'
                                </Run>
                                button
                                to begin calculating your alert.
                            </Paragraph>

                        </Section>

